parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and lag time can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to dangerous situations, especially when merging into traffic or making turns, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips and revs to high RPMs before engaging
causing a delay in acceleration
the vehicle lurches forward when the transmission finally engages
the transmission does not respond properly when the accelerator is depressed
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while slowing down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while slowing down
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the driver is trying to stop
the rear wheels leave a mark on the pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear differential oil leak can cause the differential to run dry, seize, and lock up the rear wheels, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the rear differential through pinholes
the differential runs dry
the rear wheels lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
occupants are thrown around the vehicle
occupants experience severe injuries
vehicle is totaled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and structural failure of the frame can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: Frame rusting
corrosion
or rotting
especially in areas with high humidity or salt exposure; sudden loss of control while driving; steering difficulties or jerkiness.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Steering Components (Rack and Pinion)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of steering components can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: Hard or jerky steering
difficulty turning
corrosion or rust on steering components
sudden failure of steering system.
